cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.NI, cs.Distributed Systems, cs.EDUCATION 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a community-based computing infrastructure that facilitates sharing of computational resources and data among users, and integrates batch scheduling middleware to deliver high-throughput computing services aggregated from resources distributed across wide-area networks. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on computer architecture research and education. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the Archer system utilizes wide-area networks to aggregate resources. 
- cs.Distributed Systems is relevant as the paper discusses a distributed computing infrastructure. 
- cs.EDUCATION is also relevant as the paper highlights the use of Archer for education purposes.
